<verse sid="NUM 7:87"/>all the cattle for a whole burnt offering, twelve calves, twelve rams, twelve year-old male lambs, their sacrifices and their libations and twelve male goats from the goats for sin,<verse eid="NUM 7:87"/>

<verse sid="NUM 7:88"/>all the cattle for the offering of deliverance, heifers twenty-four, rams sixty, male goats sixty, year-old ewe lambs without blemish sixty. This was the dedication of the altar, after he<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:88</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'Moyses'</char></note> filled his<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:88</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'Aaron's'</char></note> hands and after he anointed him.<verse eid="NUM 7:88"/>

<verse sid="NUM 7:89"/>When Moyses went into the tent of witness to speak with him<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:89</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'the Lord'</char></note>, then he heard the voice of the Lord speaking to him from above the propitiatory, which is upon the ark of witness, between the two cheroubim, and he was speaking to him.<verse eid="NUM 7:89"/>
