<_X_chapter sid="NUM 35">
<verse sid="NUM 35:1"/>And the Lord spoke to Moyses to the west of Moab, by the Jordan opposite Iericho, saying:<verse eid="NUM 35:1"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:2"/>Instruct the sons of Israel, and they shall give to the Leuites from the allotments of their possession cities to live in, and the suburbs<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">35:2</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Or 'environs'</char></note> of the cities around them they shall give to the Leuites-- (<verse eid="NUM 35:2"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:3"/>and the cities shall be for them to live in, and their areas set apart shall be for their cattle and for all their quadrupeds.<verse eid="NUM 35:3"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:4"/>And the areas adjoining the cities that you shall give to the Leuites shall be from the city wall and outwards, two thousand cubits all around.<verse eid="NUM 35:4"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:5"/>And you shall measure outside the city, the side towards the east, two thousand cubits, and the side towards the southwest, two thousand cubits, and the side towards the Sea, two thousand cubits, and the side towards the north, two thousand cubits, and the city in the midst of this shall be for you, and the contiguous areas of the cities-- )<verse eid="NUM 35:5"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:6"/>even the cities that you shall give to the Leuites, the six cities of places of refuge that you shall give to the murderer to flee there, and in addition to these, forty-two cities;<verse eid="NUM 35:6"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:7"/>all the cities that you shall give to the Leuites are forty-eight cities-- them and their suburbs<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">35:7</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Or 'environs'</char></note>;<verse eid="NUM 35:7"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:8"/>even the cities that you shall give from the possession of Israel's sons, many from those with many and fewer from those with fewer<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">35:8</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'many from those with many and fewer from those with fewer':  I.e. based on tribal holdings</char></note>. They shall give of their cities to the Leuites, each one according to his inheritance that they shall inherit.<verse eid="NUM 35:8"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:9"/>And the Lord spoke to Moyses, saying:<verse eid="NUM 35:9"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:10"/>Speak to the sons of Israel, and you shall say to them: As for you, you are crossing the Jordan into the land of Chanaan,<verse eid="NUM 35:10"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:11"/>and you shall set aside for yourselves cities; they shall be places of refuge for you for the murderer to flee there, everyone who strikes a soul unintentionally.<verse eid="NUM 35:11"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:12"/>And the cities shall be for you places of refuge from one doing the relative's blood duty<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">35:12</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'doing the relative's blood duty':  I.e. 'avenging the blood of a next of kin'</char></note>, and the one that commits murder will not die until he stands before the congregation for judgment.<verse eid="NUM 35:12"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:13"/>And the cities that you give as the six cities shall be places of refuge for you.<verse eid="NUM 35:13"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:14"/>Three cities you shall give beyond the Jordan, and three cities you shall give in the land of Chanaan.<verse eid="NUM 35:14"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:15"/>They shall be an asylum<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">35:15</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Or 'place of refuge'</char></note> for the sons of Israel and for the guest and for the resident alien among you. These cities shall be a place of refuge for everyone to flee there when he strikes a soul unintentionally.<verse eid="NUM 35:15"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:16"/>But if he strikes him with an iron instrument and he dies, he is a murderer; let the murderer be put to death by death.<verse eid="NUM 35:16"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:17"/>Now if he strikes him with a stone out of hand-- by which he may die-- and he dies, he is a murderer; let the murderer be put to death by death.<verse eid="NUM 35:17"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:18"/>Now if he strikes him with a wooden instrument out of hand-- from which he may die-- and he dies, he is a murderer; let the murderer be put to death by death.<verse eid="NUM 35:18"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:19"/>As for the one doing the relative's blood duty<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">35:19</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'doing the relative's blood duty':  I.e. 'avenging the blood of a next of kin'</char></note>, he shall kill the one that committed murder; when he meets up with him, he shall kill him.<verse eid="NUM 35:19"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:20"/>Now if out of enmity he pushes him and hurls at him any object from an ambush and he dies<verse eid="NUM 35:20"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:21"/>or out of rage he struck him with the hand and he dies, let the one who struck be put to death by death-- he is a murderer; let the murderer be put to death by death; the one doing the relative's blood duty<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">35:21</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'doing the relative's blood duty':  I.e. 'avenging the blood of a next of kin'</char></note> shall strike the one that committed murder when he meets him.<verse eid="NUM 35:21"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:22"/>But if he pushes him suddenly, not out of enmity, or throws at him any object not from an ambush<verse eid="NUM 35:22"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:23"/>or with any stone-- by which he may die-- unknowingly, and it falls upon him and he dies but he was not his enemy nor was he seeking to harm him,<verse eid="NUM 35:23"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:24"/>then the congregation shall judge between the striker and between the one doing the relative's blood duty<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">35:24</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'doing the relative's blood duty':  I.e. 'avenging the blood of a next of kin'</char></note>, according to these judgments,<verse eid="NUM 35:24"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:25"/>and the congregation shall rescue the one that committed murder from the one doing the relative's blood duty<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">35:25</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'doing the relative's blood duty':  I.e. 'avenging the blood of a next of kin'</char></note>. And the congregation shall restore him to the city of his place of refuge, where he fled for refuge. And he shall live there until the great priest dies, him whom they anointed with the holy oil.<verse eid="NUM 35:25"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:26"/>But if he that commits murder by an exit leaves the bounds of the city, there where he fled for refuge,<verse eid="NUM 35:26"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:27"/>and the one doing the relative's blood duty<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">35:27</char><char closed="false" style="ft">''doing the relative's blood duty'': I.e. 'avenging the blood of a next of kin'</char></note> finds him outside the bounds of the city of his refuge, and the one doing the relative's blood duty<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">35:27</char><char closed="false" style="ft">''doing the relative's blood duty': I.e. 'avenging the blood of a next of kin'</char></note> kills the one that committed murder, he is not liable.<verse eid="NUM 35:27"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:28"/>For let him live in the city of refuge until the great priest dies, and after the great priest dies, he that committed murder shall return to the land of his possession.<verse eid="NUM 35:28"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:29"/>And these things shall be for you a requirement of judgment for your generations in all your settlements.<verse eid="NUM 35:29"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:30"/>Every one, when he strikes a soul, through witnesses you shall kill the murderer, and one witness shall not bear witness against a soul that he should die.<verse eid="NUM 35:30"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:31"/>And you shall not receive ransom for a soul from the one that committed murder, liable to be killed, for he shall be put to death by death.<verse eid="NUM 35:31"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:32"/>And you shall not receive ransom to flee to a city of places of refuge to live again on the land until the great priest dies.<verse eid="NUM 35:32"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:33"/>And you shall not kill by murder the land on which you live. For this blood kills<note caller="â–¼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">35:33</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Possibly 'pollutes'</char></note> the land by murder, and the land shall not be atoned for from the blood that was shed upon it, except by the blood of the one who shed it.<verse eid="NUM 35:33"/>

<verse sid="NUM 35:34"/>And you shall not defile the land that you live upon, on which I will encamp among you, for I am the Lord, encamping in the midst of the sons of Israel.<verse eid="NUM 35:34"/>
</_X_chapter>




